cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper deals with motion detection in video streams, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a fast algorithm for randomized computation of a low-rank Dynamic Mode Decomposition (DMD), which is a linear algebra technique. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GPU acceleration for faster computation, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
